OL,3,CPaul Clark: Military heroes and the
OL,4,Cstories they tell
OL,6,FOn Saturday morning 2nd May, I
OL,7,Ftravelled from Belfast to Castlebar,
OL,8,Fin Mayo, in just under three and a
OL,9,Fhalf hours.
OL,11,FLest you think I was taking
OL,12,Funnecessary risks on the road by
OL,13,Fbreaking speed limits, I left home at
OL,14,F6am. I had allowed four hours for the
OL,15,Fjourney. Traffic was light.
OL,17,FI was an invited guest to Mayo Day:
OL,18,FMayo Military Heroes - at the National
OL,19,FMuseum of Ireland in Turlough Park, on
OL,20,Fthe outskirts of the county town.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
