OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1778094687
OL,3,CPaul Clark: Military heroes and the
OL,4,Cstories they tell
OL,6,FI am a longtime student of the Irish
OL,7,Fsoldier. The organisers have been
OL,8,Fhelpful to me in making programmes for
OL,9,FUTV, for over a quarter of a century.
OL,11,FThe event was organised by the
OL,12,FOrganisation of Ex-Service Personnel,
OL,13,FOglaigh Na hEireann (ONE). It is the
OL,14,FIrish equivalent of the Royal British
OL,15,FLegion.
OL,17,FThe lectures were open to anyone with
OL,18,Fan interest in Irish military history.
OL,19,FFor me, in my capacity as a
OL,20,Fjournalist, this has always been a
OL,21,Frich vein.
OL,26,@uD@ArguD@Mrb
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G2/16
