OL,3,CPaul Clark: Military heroes and the
OL,4,Cstories they tell
OL,6,FWhen it comes to the Irish soldier, it
OL,7,Fis tempting to think of him being in
OL,8,Fthe British Army or the Irish Defence
OL,9,FForces. This is a lazy assumption.
OL,11,FMayo men have fought in many different
OL,12,Farmies, through the generations.
OL,14,FYes, they were with Wellington at
OL,15,FWaterloo. However, the Irish soldier
OL,16,Fhas never nailed his colours to one
OL,17,Fmast. The Wild Geese have served in
OL,18,Fthe armies of France and Spain.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
