OL,3,CPaul Clark: Military heroes and the
OL,4,Cstories they tell
OL,6,FThey were in both the Union and
OL,7,FConfederate armies, during the
OL,8,FAmerican Civil War. Why? Because when
OL,9,Fthey left Ireland during The Famine -
OL,10,Fusually from Liverpool - they were
OL,11,Fguaranteed a job in America, if they
OL,12,Fsigned up to join the army. They
OL,13,Ffought for the side which paid most.
OL,14,FThe rest, as they say, is history.
OL,16,FMayo soldiers formed the backbone of
OL,17,FThe Connaught Rangers. This Irish
OL,18,FRegiment was engaged in South Africa,
OL,19,Fduring The Boer War (1899-1902). It
OL,20,Fwas an imperial war, so, naturally,
OL,21,Fthe Irish were fighting on both sides.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G5/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
