OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1778094687
OL,3,CPaul Clark: Military heroes and the
OL,4,Cstories they tell
OL,6,FThe Irish war of independence did not
OL,7,Fbring the fighting to an end. The
OL,8,FAnglo Irish Treaty led to the Irish
OL,9,FCivil War. Are you for The Treaty, or
OL,10,Fagainst it? Mayo men fought on both
OL,11,Fsides. The echoes of that time divided
OL,12,Ffamilies then - and still do, today.
OL,13,FHistory will never be in the past!
OL,15,FThe man most people came to hear was
OL,16,FCaptain Noel Carey. He served with UN
OL,17,FForces in the Congo. The Battle of
OL,18,FJadotville in 1961 was the most
OL,19,Fsignificant action involving the Irish
OL,20,FDefence Forces since the Civil War.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G7/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
