OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1778094687
OL,3,CPaul Clark: Military heroes and the
OL,4,Cstories they tell
OL,6,FThe ceremony was attended by The Irish
OL,7,FGuards. On their way west, they paid
OL,8,Ftheir respects to a colleague.
OL,10,FIan Malone was from Dublin. He wanted
OL,11,Fto be a soldier, but was rejected by
OL,12,FThe Irish Defence Forces. He joined
OL,13,FThe Irish Guards, and was killed in
OL,14,FIraq. His funeral, in 2003, was the
OL,15,Ffirst time, since 1922, that uniformed
OL,16,FBritish soldiers had been seen in
OL,17,FDublin.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}           G13/16
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
